The paper discusses the use of recurrent neural network architectures for event-sequence processing, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on the use of continuous-time recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in the fields of control systems and robotics, and are therefore likely to be classified under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of these architectures for processing event sequences, which is a topic that is relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
